]As an Ennea 8, you have no problem with powerand will naturally gravitate towards positions ofleadership and authority. Being in a leadership role is
almost second nature to you. In a position ofauthority you will systematically grow your influenceand sphere of control.
]There is a vitality and lust for life that youexude. You show up in a room in a way that may seem
“larger than life”. You live passionately.
]You respond to strength and independence inothers. In your relationships, this strength ofcharacter will allow you to give your support andprotection to others. You stand up to defend your
team, as long as they are coming to the party andshowing their strength of character.
]You come across as confident and self-assured,making it easy for others to have confidence in yourabilities.
]As an Ennea 8 you are willing to be forceful inservice of others and your ideals or goals. You knowwhat you stand for and will generally project a huge
amount of certainty in the way you express this toothers.
]Your need to be in control will enable you to notonly control outcome, but also your personal space,possessions and the broader environment in which you
operate. This should enable you to make a diﬀerence ona strategic level.
]You are able to make unsentimental decisions andtake risks when needed. You are generally very focusedon the present, preferring not to dwell in the past or
obsess about the future.
]When you apply your focus and intent to aproblem or issue, this enables revolutionary activism.You will work through obstacles with fervour and intent.You will overcome your challenges and draw strengthfrom your ability to persevere and see things through.
The Ennea 8 has the following strengths and positive qualities
This section helps you tap into and appreciate the strengths and positive aspects of your Enneagram style.These strengths, when harnessed in a healthy and balanced way will support your wellbeing, goals andrelationships. To help you harness these strengths, ask yourself the following questions:● How can I use this strength to assist me in overcoming my current challenges?
● What habits and behaviours support me in my capacity to harness these strengths?
● How easy or diﬀicult is it for me to acknowledge and appreciate my good, true and beautiful qualities?
● What does each strength look like when over-utilised or applied in an unhealthy way?
